{"name": "st-cookie", "metadata": {"name": "st-cookie", "version": "0.2.3", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://github.com/xtliu97/st_cookie", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Streamlit Cookie Writer and Reader", "upload_time": 1732846243}, "documentation": ["# st_cookie \n## What \n`st_cookie` is a Python package that allows you to store and retrieve data in a cookie. \n\n## Installation\n```bash\npip install st-cookie\n```\n\n## Usage\n- import\n```python\nfrom st_cookie import cookie_manager\n```\n\n- Usage 1  \nUse `cookie_manager.load_to_session_state()` to load all the variables from cookies to session state. Use `cookie_manager.update()` to update session states to cookies with `on_change` or `on_click` callback of streamlit components.\n```python\ncookie_manager.load_to_session_state()\n\nst.checkbox(\n    \"enabled\",\n    key=\"my_checkbox\",\n    on_change=lambda: cookie_manager.update(\"my_checkbox\"),\n)\n```\n\n- Usage 2  \nUse context manager `cookie_manager.sync()` to sync variables to between cookies and session states.\n```python\nwith cookie_manager.sync(\"my_textinput\", \"my_number\"):\n    st.text_input(\"Enter text\", key=\"my_textinput\")\n    st.number_input(\"Enter number\", key=\"my_number\")\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "setup", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "st_cookie", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "st_cookie.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "st_cookie.cookie_manager", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "st_cookie.cookie_manager", "xref": {"fqname": "st_cookie.cookie_manager", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "st_cookie.core", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "st_cookie.core.obj_to_txt", "asynchronous": fals